trait_name: leaf nitrogen content per leaf dry mass
method: Canopy N% was estimated with the Carnegie Airborne Observatory Airborne Taxonomic Mapping System (CAO-AToMs) onboard a Dornier 228 Aircraft. lamina thickness is the thickness of the leaf lamina measured in regions that do not include primary or secondary veins.  Species means of the individual means of two leaves per individual for the lamina portion used in shearing test.
lamina fracture toughness is the work to fracture leaf tissue divided by fracture area (lamina thickness * length of fracture). Species means of the individual means of two leaves per individual.
